In the Circuit Court of the United States for the District of Washington. Northern Division.
No. 776
In the Matter of the application of Salfest A. Sylvester for a writ of habeas corpus.
ORDER DISCHARGING PRISONER under writ of habeas corpus.
This matter coming on regularly to be heard this 3rd day of July, 1899, upon the writ of habeas corpus issued herein, the petitioner appearing by his counsel R.B. Albertson, Esq., and the respondents by their counsel John B. Hart, Esq., and a return to said writ having been filed by the respondents, and a motion to quash said return and for the discharge of the prisoner from the restraint under the warrant set forth by said return having been made and filed by the petitioner And it appearing to the court that said return does not show sufficient cause for the restraint of the prisoner in that the requisition papers in said matter are not made a part thereof, and in that the warrant under which the petitioner is held is void on its face; and the court being fully advised in the premises, grants said motion. Wherefore it is ordered, considered and adjudged that said return be and the same is hereby quashed and set aside and that the petitioner be released from the custody under said warrant and that the respondents and all other persons be and they are hereby restrained from holding the petitioner further under said warrant; and that the petitioner recover of and from the respondents his costs and disbursements herein.
And now at this time counsel for respondents states in open court that he does not desire to appeal from the foregoing order, and further states that he is satisfied that the Governor of North Dakota and the authorities of that States intend to prosecute
-1-
petitioner under the same charge referred to in said warrant and to make a new demand upon the Governor of the State of Washington for a writ of extradition under which the petitioner shall be returned to North Dakota for trial; and said counsel further moves the court that pending communication between him and the Governor of North Dakota petitioner be remanded to the custody of the Sheriff of King County. Said counsel for the petitioner objects to said motion on the ground that since the discharge of the petitioner from custody under said former warrant he is entitled to his liberty forthwith, and on the ground that there is no process of law under which he can be held further in that there are no extradition proceedings now pending against the petitoner. Upon argument the court grants said motion, and does now order the petitioner to be remanded to the custody of the Sheriff of King County, until Wednesday, the 5th day of July, 1899, at 3 o'clock p.m., when he shall again be brought before the court to obey such order as the court may then make herein. To this order of the court the petitioner through his counsel excepts, and said exception is allowed.
done in open court this 3rd day of July, 1899.
C. H. Hanford Judge
Tx.
